A couple born in beds next to each other on the same day in the same hospital ended up getting married - and will next week celebrate their 60th birthdays together.

Dave O'Callaghan and Jane Hammond were both born at the Mowbray Maternity Hospital in Exeter, Devon - which has since closed - on January 26, 1955, but didn't meet again until they were 17.

The pair soon fell in love and were engaged at 21, before marrying the next year. 

