The couple, of Exeter, Devon, have been married for 38 years and are celebrating their joint birthday on Monday.They have two children, Lydia, 29, and Imogen, 25.

Ms Hammond said the biggest advantage of their parallel existence is that they never forget each other's birthdays.

When she asked her husband-to-be's birthday, as first 'I didn't believe him', but the couple have 'never really made much of it'.

However, she acknowledges that being 'born in the same hospital on the same day and in the same year is a bizarre coincidence'.

'People are very surprised when we tell them our story. Their reactions make us realise how rare and special it is.

